spans.text: Thy Daughter , circling thrice thy tomb , With mystic rites of thrilling power
he not , in whisper deep , That dread companion of thy sleep ? — Fallen before its edge thy foes , Idly does it now repose In the dark tomb with thee ? — awake
That dread companion of thy sleep ? — Fallen before its edge thy foes , Idly does it now repose In the dark tomb with thee ? — awake
Deaf to the low sepulchral sound ? — HERVARDOR , — HIARVARDOR , — hear
that drank their gore ? — Living , — why , to MAGIC RHYME
Amid Battle's yell The charmed , the fatal Weapon
if thy intrepid zeal May win the all-subduing Steel
hides thee in this silent hall
thy Mother's frame When the FATAL

that joys when Foes assail , Sword , that scorns the ribbed mail

Scorn of the sepulchral flames , Lest their force around thee swell , Punishing thy daring spell
Thou , whose awless voice proclaims Scorn of the sepulchral flames , Lest their force around thee swell , Punishing thy daring spell , And thy mortal form
exultation vain , Fatal , fatal shall be found To thee , and thine
Nor let strife , and bitter scorn , Amid Herva's offspring , yet unborn
Winters , drain Driving snow , or drenching rain
— for these blue fires infest The troubled tomb's presumptuous Guest ; As of step profane aware , Round me , more and more , they glare
